$ ISO 9949

*ISO/IEC/IEEE 9945* defines a standard operating system interface and environment, including a command interpreter (aka → Linux/shell[shell])
and common utility programs to support applications portability at the source code level.

ISO 9949 is redacted(?) by the technical committee → https://www.iso.org/committee/45202.html[ISO/IEC JTC 1/SC 22] (Programming languages, their environments and system software interfaces)

{ Areas that are not included in the scope of ISO 9949

  The following areas are explicitely excluded from the scoe of ISO 9949:
   • → development/GUI[Graphics interfaces]
   • → development/databases[Database] management system interfaces
   • Record I/O considerations
   • Object or binary code portability
   • System configuration and resource availability.

}
sa:
  → https://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/9699919799/basedefs/V1_chap01.html[POSIX.1-2017]
